      • loadProgressCheck

        public static ProgressCheck loadProgressCheck(String impl,
                                              org.json.JSONObject config,
                                              ClassLoader classLoader)
                                       throws Exception
        Attempt to load a ProgressCheck from a particular class loader. The impl value is first tried as a fully-qualified class name, and if a Class<?> is found, it is first checked for the ProgressCheckFactory interface, and then for the ProgressCheck interface. If a class is not found, Locator assumes the impl value represents a resource name for an Invocable script, and attempts to create a ScriptProgressCheck from it.
        Parameters:
        impl - className or resourceName
        config - provide an optional config object (may be ignored by the check.)
        classLoader - a specific classLoader to use
        Returns:
        a new ProgressCheck instance for the given name
        Throws:
        Exception - on any error or failure to find a resource for given name.
